            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1968-12-16T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1960-04-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="78" subtype="editorial-note"
                type="document" xml:id="d78">
                <head>78. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>An undated and unsigned memorandum entitled the “Death of <persName
                        corresp="#p_LPE_1">Patrice Lumumba</persName>” was sent to Director of
                    Central Intelligence <persName corresp="#p_DAW_1">Dulles</persName> under cover
                    of a note dated March 7, 1961, which reads: “You were asking that the Division
                    get together in a memorandum our best estimate of the actual facts and
                    circumstances surrounding the death of <persName corresp="#p_LPE_1">Patrice
                        Lumumba</persName>. This memorandum is attached and I am not sure whether
                    you intended to send it to the President or not. FMC” A stamped notation on the
                    original indicates that <persName corresp="#p_DAW_1">Dulles</persName> saw it on
                    March 8, but it bears no indication that it was sent to the President. (Central
                    Intelligence Agency Files, Job 86B00975R, <gloss target="#t_DCIOCA_1"
                        >DCI/OCA</gloss> Registry, Box 2, Folder 18, Review Staff Files,
                    Assassinations, Vol. I) The memorandum is printed as <ref
                        target="frus1961-63v20#d44">Document 44 in <hi rend="italic">Foreign
                            Relations,</hi> 1961–1963, volume XX, Congo Crisis</ref>, pages
                    93–94.</p>
            </div>
